class Solution {
    public int[] constructRectangle(int area) {
        int L = 1;
        int W = area;
        while (L * W < area) {
            W--;
        }
        return new int[]{L, W};
    }
}
```

efficiency: MEDIUM
time complexity: O(log(area))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

We start with L = 1 and W = area. Then, we enter a while loop that continues until the product of L and W is greater than the target area. In each iteration, we decrease W by 1. This ensures that the area is reduced by half in each iteration, which guarantees that the area will eventually become 1 (when L * W = area). After the loop, L and W will represent the optimal dimensions of the rectangle. We return them as an array [L, W].

